<|startoftext|>Dish: wonderful cheddar cheese chocolate dip
Directions: combine the cheeses , butter , mustard , cayenne and salt
beat with the electric mixer on medium speed until fluffy , and then add 2 1 / 2 cups milk
stir-fry a few more minutes on medium , to ensure there is no tongue burn
add the milk slowly to the cheeses and continue to stir it in gradually
add the coconut milk , lemon juice , water and melted butter to the butter mix and mix everything until blended
spread dough about the size of a large golf ball on the counter-top of a 12-by-12-square baking pan
put a strip of waxed paper on the countertop , with the dip, to keep it from sticking
put the dip in the oven at 175C, for about 2 hours
to reduce the time it takes to do the dip once, simply turn the oven off for about 45 minutes and you will see the dip come out a little thicker and more opaque
